60.1	The_Fog_of_War	The Fog of War	The Fog of War: Eleven Lessons from the Life of Robert S. McNamara is a 2003 American documentary film about the life and times of former U.S. Secretary of Defense Robert S. McNamara as well as illustrating his observations of the nature of modern warfare. The film was directed by Errol Morris and the original score is by Philip Glass.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/71/Fog_of_war.jpg/220px-Fog_of_war.jpg
